    "plan_content": "Here is my complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `uv cache stats` Subcommand\n\n### What I found in the codebase\n\n- **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` (lines 878–952):** `CacheCommand` enum ends with `Size(SizeArgs)` at line 904; `SizeArgs` struct is defined at lines 947–952 with exactly the `human` bool field and arg attributes needed for `StatsArgs`.\n- **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_size.rs`:** The exact implementation template — uses `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()`, `human_readable_bytes`, `printer.stdout_important()`, and returns `ExitStatus::Success`. It also has a `preview` guard we do **not** need for `cache_stats`.\n- **`crates/uv-cache/src/lib.rs`:** `CacheBucket::iter()` yields 11 variants; `Cache::bucket(bucket)` returns a `PathBuf`; `Display` for `CacheBucket` produces strings like `wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`, etc.\n- **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`:** `CacheCommand::Size(args)` dispatches to `commands::cache_size(&cache, args.human, printer, globals.preview)` — we follow the same pattern minus `globals.preview`.\n\n### 4 changes required\n\n1. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + add `StatsArgs` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`) after it.\n\n2. **Create `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** — New file with `pub(crate) fn cache_stats(cache, human_readable, printer)` that loops `CacheBucket::iter()`, computes per-bucket size with `DiskUsage`, prints `{bucket}: {size}` per line, then prints `total: {size}`.\n\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` alongside the `cache_size` declarations.\n\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` after the `Size` arm, calling `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)`.",
